
[1]handkerchief

   HAND'KERCHIEF, n. [hand and kerchief. See Kerchief.]

   1. A piece of cloth, usually silk or linen, carried about the person
   for the purpose of cleaning the face or hands, as occasion requires.

   2. A piece of cloth to be worn about the neck, and sometimes called a
   neckerchief.
